  <div class="about sec">
    <div class="sec-t">About</div>
    <p>Fjellheisen is a cable car system connecting <strong>Solliveien 12 in Tromsdalen</strong> to the summit of Storsteinen mountain, 421 metres above sea level. The gondola carries up to 28 passengers per car and completes the 752-metre journey in approximately 4 minutes, running at a capacity of up to 400 persons per hour. The cable car operates daily from 09:00 to midnight, with the summit café (Fjellstua) open until 23:30.</p>
    <p>From Storsteinen, the platform offers an unobstructed 360-degree view over <strong>Tromsø island, the Tromsøysundet strait, surrounding fjords, and the Lyngen Alps</strong>. The midnight sun is visible from the summit from approximately 20 May to 22 July, when the full solar disc remains above the horizon for 24 hours. During the polar night season (September–April), the elevated position above the city's light pollution makes it one of Tromsø's primary aurora borealis viewing locations. Optimal aurora activity typically occurs between 18:00 and 02:00.</p>
    <p>The operator, Fjellheisen AS, is currently in the planning phase of <strong>Fjellheisen 2.0</strong>, a reconstruction project that will replace the existing gondola system. During this period, wheelchair accessibility is suspended. A shuttle bus service from Tromsø Harbour operates daily during the winter season (15 September–31 March). Alternative access is possible on foot (approximately 45 minutes from the city centre) or by taxi (approximately 10 minutes, NOK 150–250 from the centre).</p>
  </div>

  <div class="sec">
    <div class="sec-t">Crowd levels by day</div>
