      <div class="crowd-row"><span class="crowd-day">Tue</span><div class="crowd-bar"><div class="crowd-fill c-low" style="width:30%"></div></div><span class="crowd-lbl c-low-l">Quiet</span></div>
      <div class="crowd-row"><span class="crowd-day">Wed</span><div class="crowd-bar"><div class="crowd-fill c-med" style="width:45%"></div></div><span class="crowd-lbl c-med-l">Moderate</span></div>
      <div class="crowd-row"><span class="crowd-day">Thu</span><div class="crowd-bar"><div class="crowd-fill c-med" style="width:50%"></div></div><span class="crowd-lbl c-med-l">Moderate</span></div>
      <div class="crowd-row"><span class="crowd-day">Fri</span><div class="crowd-bar"><div class="crowd-fill c-high" style="width:75%"></div></div><span class="crowd-lbl c-high-l">Busy</span></div>
      <div class="crowd-row"><span class="crowd-day">Sat</span><div class="crowd-bar"><div class="crowd-fill c-high" style="width:95%"></div></div><span class="crowd-lbl c-high-l">Peak</span></div>
      <div class="crowd-row"><span class="crowd-day">Sun</span><div class="crowd-bar"><div class="crowd-fill c-high" style="width:85%"></div></div><span class="crowd-lbl c-high-l">Busy</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="crowd-tip"><strong>Best time:</strong> Monday and Tuesday mornings between 09:00–11:00 see the shortest queues. Saturday afternoons (13:00–17:00) and clear-sky aurora evenings in winter are the busiest periods. The gondola can close without notice in high winds — check fjellheisen.no on the day of your visit.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="venue-photo-bottom"></div>

  <div class="sec">
    <div class="sec-t">FAQ</div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">How much does Fjellheisen Cable Car cost?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">Adult round-trip: NOK 595 (approx. €53.00). Child 6–17 round-trip: NOK 285 (approx. €25.50). Family 2+2 round-trip: NOK 1,255 (approx. €111.50). One-way adult: NOK 380. Children under 6 ride free. Book at book.fjellheisen.no to avoid reseller markups.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">How do I get to Fjellheisen from Tromsø city centre?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">The lower station is at Solliveien 12, Tromsdalen. Walking from the city centre takes approximately 45 minutes. A shuttle bus (NOK 100 adult, NOK 50 child) runs from Tromsø Harbour daily during winter season (15 Sep–31 Mar). Bus 26 from Torgsenteret stops at the 'Fjellheisen' stop. A taxi from the centre takes approximately 10 minutes and costs NOK 150–250.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">What are the opening hours for Fjellheisen?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">The gondola operates daily 09:00–00:00. The summit café (Fjellstua) is open daily 09:00–23:30. The cable car may close without notice during high winds or maintenance. Check fjellheisen.no on the day of your visit for current status.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fq">
      <div class="fq-q">Can I see the Northern Lights from Fjellheisen?</div>
      <div class="fq-a">The Storsteinen summit is one of Tromsø's highest easily accessible viewpoints. Aurora activity is possible from September to April when skies are clear. The gondola runs until midnight, allowing evening viewing. No aurora sightings are guaranteed — conditions depend on solar activity, cloud cover, and light pollution. Check aurora forecasts independently before booking an evening trip.</div>
    </div>
